[With all of the positive deer we have had in Michigan lately, it is most amazing this is the 1st free-ranging animal that has been confirmed to have the disease. As such, it is likely that we may see more reports in free-range deer. While it may have been in free-range deer for some time, it is the 1st diagnosed. The DNR will test as many free-range deer as possible, in other words, kill them to test them. It is understandable that they want to know the extent of the disease, but it might be better to wait until hunting season and then do the testing.

Michigan may be located on a map at: http://healthmap.org/r/awKb - Mod.TG]
